HEADWORD: Exolete
<hw>Ex"o*lete</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exoletus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exolescere</ets> to grow out, grow
out of use; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>olescere</ets> to grow.]</ety>
<def>Obsolete; out of use; state; insipid.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

